The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning algorithms and their performance on standard benchmarks. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm that simplifies existing algorithms and achieves state-of-the-art performance on challenging tasks. This suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
